=E2=80=9Cif you=E2=80=99re enforcing, that means showing up with a truck an=
d hoping the cows are still there.=E2=80=9D ...
A securitisation portfolio manager, not involved in the deal, said: =E2=80=
=9CIf it had a PIK coupon in steak I would buy that PA [personal account]=
=E2=80=9D.

I have given you only a small sampling of the cow puns in the piece. I feel=
 like using cows as collateral is not=C2=A0vastly more challenging, concept=
ually, than securitizing, like, auto loans, or credit card receivables for =
that matter. A lot of stuff in finance rests on many layers of abstraction,=
 at the bottom of which is =E2=80=9Cif they don=E2=80=99t pay you back, you=
 gotta show up with a truck.=E2=80=9D But the cows allow for more jokes abo=
ut payment-in-steak coupons.

 =20
   =20
      Lemonhead of macro
   =20
 =20

Man, I don=E2=80=99t know. We talked yesterday about James Fishback, a guy =
who has variously sued and been sued by Greenlight Capital over his claims =
that he was Greenlight=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Chead of macro.=E2=80=9D I quoted =
a passage from Greenlight=E2=80=99s latest lawsuit against Fishback that al=
leged that he did a bad job on something called =E2=80=9Cthe Jelly Donut As=
signment=E2=80=9D in July 2023. That assignment was not explained further, =
though I noted that Greenlight=E2=80=99s founder, David Einhorn, has some h=
istory with jelly donuts as a macroeconomic metaphor.=C2=A0The Jelly Donut =
Assignment led to Fishback=E2=80=99s departure from Greenlight, after which=
 he started his own hedge fund, Azoria. Anyway here=E2=80=99s an Axios arti=
cle from October 2023:

The Fed has a Lemonhead problem. That's the term that one investor is using=
 to explain why the central bank's historic rate-hiking campaign hasn't don=
e more damage to the economy (yet).
How it works: Like the candy, rate hikes start off sour =E2=80=94 the S&P f=
ell 19% last year; the tech industry shed a lot of jobs. But then they turn=
 sweet =E2=80=94 that's where we are now, with consumer spending and the la=
bor market still looking relatively solid.
=E2=80=9CThe full effect of higher rates is not being felt by consumers and=
 businesses,=E2=80=9D said James Fishback, founder and chief investment off=
icer (and candy theorist) at Azoria Partners, a global macro hedge fund.

Okay. Okay. Okay! If you have any other sweet-treat-related macroeconomic t=
heories I do not want to hear them. Meanwhile on X, Fishback keeps posting.=
 Here=E2=80=99s his 2022 comp letter ($975,000 total pay). And here he is a=
dmitting that he did a bad job on the Jelly Donut Assignment, saying =E2=80=
=9CI dragged my feet on David=E2=80=99s =E2=80=98macro research projects=E2=
=80=99 because they were laughably stupid=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CI am a macr=
o trader not some washed-up billionaire=E2=80=99s ghost writer.=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0

